1352
01:19:46,320 --> 01:19:49,640
- Let's whack him.
- Hey, this ain't Scarface, all right?

1353
01:19:50,960 --> 01:19:54,320
You got a plan?

1354
01:19:54,400 --> 01:19:58,040
Big con.
Dick Dodge is the mark.

1355
01:19:58,120 --> 01:20:00,640
- Dick Dodge?
- Aren't we getting out
of our league here, man?

1356
01:20:00,680 --> 01:20:02,600
This guy's been doin'
the big con for over 30 years.

1357
01:20:02,680 --> 01:20:05,240
Mmm, cuz, these politicians,

1358
01:20:05,320 --> 01:20:08,040
these are some serious slick fish.

1359
01:20:08,080 --> 01:20:10,760
Wait a second. Is everybody
goin' soft here all of a sudden?

1360
01:20:10,840 --> 01:20:13,440
Are you all a bunch
of fuckin' incumbents now?

1361
01:20:13,520 --> 01:20:16,040
Listen, Thursday, Dick Dodge
is at the arts caucus, all right?

1362
01:20:16,120 --> 01:20:19,160
I need to know how long it takes
to get from there to the EPA building.

1363
01:20:19,240 --> 01:20:21,040
All right, Armando?
Okay, now.

1364
01:20:21,120 --> 01:20:24,080
Loretta, get some information
on the EPA and give that to the roper.

1365
01:20:24,160 --> 01:20:26,240
I got a list of equipment
I want you to go get.

1366
01:20:26,320 --> 01:20:28,320
- Crazy, baby.
- Hey.

1367
01:20:28,400 --> 01:20:32,040
Don't we need a new roper?
I mean, hey, look, everybody
around here knows our faces.

1368
01:20:32,120 --> 01:20:35,200
- [Car Horn Honking]
- Speak of the devil.

1369
01:20:40,080 --> 01:20:42,840
- My man!
- What up, T?

1370
01:20:42,920 --> 01:20:46,880
- Homer!
- What's up?

1371
01:20:49,360 --> 01:20:53,520
Hey, Dick.
Eli Hawkins got his tail...

1372
01:20:53,600 --> 01:20:56,200
- Caught in a crack, huh?
- He did.

1373
01:20:56,280 --> 01:20:59,400
- And you kept my name out of it?
- I did.

1374
01:20:59,480 --> 01:21:01,640
- So I owe you?
- You do.

1375
01:21:06,000 --> 01:21:08,680
This hearing of the committee on Power
and Industry will come to order.

1376
01:21:08,720 --> 01:21:12,320
[Dodge] The health
of America's insurance industry...

1377
01:21:12,400 --> 01:21:16,840
Hey, come here. Somethin' came up.
I got a call from an EPA guy.

1378
01:21:16,880 --> 01:21:19,120
Said he heard how fast
I bailed on the power lines.

1379
01:21:19,200 --> 01:21:21,360
He's got something
really hot for me.

1380
01:21:21,440 --> 01:21:25,240
He wants to meet me outta the office,
after business hours, like tonight.

1381
01:21:29,200 --> 01:21:31,560
[Thomas]
Mr. Whitney?

1382
01:21:31,600 --> 01:21:33,760
You said you'd be alone.

1383
01:21:33,840 --> 01:21:35,840
What is he doin' here?
What is he, a cop?

1384
01:21:35,880 --> 01:21:39,120
You wearin' a wire?
You wearin' a goddamn wire?

1385
01:21:39,200 --> 01:21:41,040
Relax, Mr. Whitney,
I'm not wired.

1386
01:21:41,120 --> 01:21:43,520
Yeah?

1387
01:21:43,600 --> 01:21:46,080
Well, let's see.

1388
01:21:46,160 --> 01:21:48,880
I know you got it.
I just gotta find it, that's all.

1389
01:21:50,720 --> 01:21:53,840
- Get your hands off me!
- Hey, man, I told ya he's okay.

1390
01:21:53,920 --> 01:21:55,800
He's not wired.
Look. He has no wire here.

1391
01:21:55,880 --> 01:21:58,840
No wire. You can trust him.
Look at this guy.

1392
01:21:58,920 --> 01:22:03,240
He's got fire engines
on his drawers. This is a good man.
Now cool it. Just relax.

1393
01:22:03,320 --> 01:22:05,600
Is this gonna be
something we can use?

1394
01:22:05,640 --> 01:22:08,720
Your friends at the power company
would be very interested.

1395
01:22:11,640 --> 01:22:16,160
- Talk to me.
- All right.

1396
01:22:16,200 --> 01:22:19,080
The White House
is putting heat on the EPA.

1397
01:22:19,160 --> 01:22:21,920
Now we're gonna announce
a major investigation...

1398
01:22:22,000 --> 01:22:24,680
on the relation between power lines
and cancer clusters.

1399
01:22:35,640 --> 01:22:38,760
Mrs. Dodge, it's Arthur Reinhardt.
May I please speak to the chairman?

1400
01:22:42,680 --> 01:22:45,760
[Woman On Intercom]
Mr. Andersen? Mr. Bridges is on one.

1401
01:22:45,840 --> 01:22:48,360
Zeke!
How in the hell are ya?

1402
01:22:48,440 --> 01:22:51,120
[As Zeke] I'm madder than a baptist
in a brothel, you som-bitch!

1403
01:22:51,200 --> 01:22:55,680
Olaf! You hear about this EPA bullshit?
Why, it could ruin Gulf Coast Power!

1404
01:22:55,720 --> 01:22:58,560
They're goin' ahead with this goddamn
power lines investigation.

1405
01:22:58,600 --> 01:23:01,640
I thought we had this settled.
They don't have any proof.

1406
01:23:01,720 --> 01:23:03,640
They ain't lookin' for proof! They're
lookin' for dinner and we're it!

1407
01:23:03,720 --> 01:23:06,320
I tell ya, I'm about as crazy
as a dog in a hubcap factory.

1408
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:10,200
[Sighing]
Ah, shit.

1409
01:23:10,280 --> 01:23:13,160
All right, Zeke.

1410
01:23:13,240 --> 01:23:15,680
Zeke, I'm goin' up to D.C.
for the clean air hearings anyway.

1411
01:23:15,760 --> 01:23:18,120
I'll talk to Dodge.

1412
01:23:19,640 --> 01:23:21,560
- Ya got a second?
- Yeah.

1413
01:23:21,640 --> 01:23:23,880
Okay, I heard something. And I know
there's some business in it.

1414
01:23:23,960 --> 01:23:28,400
- I'm listening.
- EPA, launching a big
investigation on power lines.

1415
01:23:28,480 --> 01:23:31,360
- They're gettin' a lot
of pressure from the White House.
- That's very interesting.

1416
01:23:31,440 --> 01:23:34,640
I heard the same thing.

1417
01:23:34,720 --> 01:23:36,920
- Nothing gets by you, does it?
- Not much.

1418
01:23:37,000 --> 01:23:40,640
But thank you, son.
I appreciate your sharing that with me.

1419
01:23:40,680 --> 01:23:43,720
Okay, so, there's probably
something in it for us.

1420
01:23:43,800 --> 01:23:46,720
Thomas, if we got the EPA
off Olaf Andersen's back,

1421
01:23:46,760 --> 01:23:49,480
he'd be extremely
appreciative.

1422
01:23:49,560 --> 01:23:53,640
- So... how do we go about doin' that?
- My committee.

1423
01:23:53,720 --> 01:23:57,120
We audit their funding.
Hell, I got him by the balls.

1424
01:23:57,160 --> 01:23:59,400
- So you're just gonna
rip their balls o...
- Oh, no, no, no.

1425
01:23:59,440 --> 01:24:02,320
Thomas, persuasion.

1426
01:24:02,400 --> 01:24:05,800
- Strenuous persuasion.
- Oh, now, that's allowed.

1427
01:24:05,880 --> 01:24:08,680
Persuasion, yes.
Intimidation, no.

1428
01:24:08,760 --> 01:24:11,400
But... it's a gray area.

1429
01:24:11,480 --> 01:24:13,800
- Who's to say which is which?
- Oh!

1430
01:24:13,880 --> 01:24:17,000
Persuasion. You can't rip 'em out.
You have to persuade 'em out.

1431
01:24:17,080 --> 01:24:20,080
Hey, Dick, is there somebody
you can call to make sure...

1432
01:24:20,160 --> 01:24:22,120
the EPA's really doing
the investigation?

1433
01:24:22,200 --> 01:24:24,520
- Of course. He oughta be in by now.
- Who?

1434
01:24:24,600 --> 01:24:29,680
Skeeter Warburton, of course.
Always go straight to the top, son.

1435
01:24:29,760 --> 01:24:34,040
Oh, a little outta
my league, Dick.

1436
01:24:39,400 --> 01:24:41,200
Hey.

1437
01:24:42,240 --> 01:24:43,960
Watch it.

1438
01:24:44,040 --> 01:24:46,560
Let's go!

1439
01:24:49,200 --> 01:24:52,000
[Hattie]
Congressman Dodge?

1440
01:24:52,080 --> 01:24:54,960
Oh, uh, uh, Mrs. Rifkin
from the, uh...

1441
01:24:55,040 --> 01:24:57,320
Silver Foxes. You remember,

1442
01:24:57,400 --> 01:25:00,400
America's second-largest
seniors' organization...

1443
01:25:00,480 --> 01:25:04,000
with members in every district
in Florida, including yours.

1444
01:25:04,080 --> 01:25:07,520
Oh, yes, of course. It's a marvelous
organization, just marvelous.

1445
01:25:07,600 --> 01:25:10,960
- Well, it's always a pleasure to see...
- I need to talk to you.

1446
01:25:11,040 --> 01:25:14,760
Yes, I'd like that very much,
but right now I'm in a rush
to get back to my office.

1447
01:25:14,800 --> 01:25:18,440
- You call for an appointment.
We'll get together...
- This won't take a second.

1448
01:25:18,480 --> 01:25:21,240
- Could I just walk ya to your office?
- Uh, well...

1449
01:25:21,320 --> 01:25:23,400
- That'd be fine.
- Oh, good.

1450
01:25:43,960 --> 01:25:47,560
If the FDA would just agree
to look at the new support hose,

1451
01:25:47,600 --> 01:25:50,280
we'd feel like
we made some progress.

1452
01:25:50,360 --> 01:25:54,200
Indeed, you know, Mrs. Rifkin, I'm
always so excited to hear your views,

1453
01:25:54,280 --> 01:25:56,520
but really, dear,
I've got to run.

1454
01:25:56,600 --> 01:25:58,640
So run,
who's keeping you?

1455
01:25:58,720 --> 01:26:02,240
So don't be a stranger.
Keep in touch.

1456
01:26:15,520 --> 01:26:17,360
[Elevator Bell Ringing]

1457
01:26:21,320 --> 01:26:24,240
[Elevator Bell Ringing]

1458
01:26:33,600 --> 01:26:36,000
[Coin Clanging]

1459
01:26:44,120 --> 01:26:46,920
Kimberly, can you get me
Skeeter Warburton on the phone, please?

1460
01:26:46,960 --> 01:26:48,880
Right away, Chairman Dodge.

1461
01:26:50,320 --> 01:26:54,400
- Uh, sweep for radon?
- Radon? I'm sorry, l...

1462
01:26:54,440 --> 01:26:56,360
I don't recall.

1463
01:26:56,440 --> 01:26:58,800
Do you have a work order?

1464
01:26:58,880 --> 01:27:01,520
Oh, no, uh,
Supervisor said, uh...

1465
01:27:01,600 --> 01:27:04,040
Supervisor said ain't supposed
to be no paperwork on this...

1466
01:27:04,120 --> 01:27:06,480
'cause something about
y'all killed some radon study.

1467
01:27:06,560 --> 01:27:08,840
Well, we did delete
a few minor budget items.

1468
01:27:08,920 --> 01:27:10,880
Hey, how's it gonna look
to the other people...

1469
01:27:10,920 --> 01:27:14,640
if they find out I swept your office
for radon, didn't do everybody else's?

1470
01:27:14,720 --> 01:27:17,680
- How that gonna look, Mr. Warburton?
- Point taken. Go right ahead.

1471
01:27:17,760 --> 01:27:20,040
You better step outside. I gotta spray
some nasty shit. Look at that.

1472
01:27:20,080 --> 01:27:22,800
Uh-huh.

1473
01:27:22,880 --> 01:27:25,600
Ah, Brenda? I'm stepping out
for a few minutes.

1474
01:27:25,680 --> 01:27:29,000
Yeah, Brenda, don't come in here, 'cause
you may get some of this shit on ya.

1475
01:27:38,520 --> 01:27:40,640
[As Warburton]
Ah, Brenda, I've changed my mind.

1476
01:27:40,720 --> 01:27:44,800
- I'm expecting a call from...
- Mr. Warburton,
Chairman Dodge is on line two.

1477
01:27:44,880 --> 01:27:48,200
Oh, speak of the devil.
Put him through.

1478
01:27:48,280 --> 01:27:50,560
Afternoon, Mr. Chairman.
Skeeter here.

1479
01:27:50,600 --> 01:27:52,520
I need a straight answer
from you, Skeeter.

1480
01:27:52,560 --> 01:27:54,480
Is the White House
on your back about power lines?

1481
01:27:54,520 --> 01:27:57,680
- Are we off the record, Mr. Chairman?
- Of course.

1482
01:27:57,760 --> 01:28:01,600
I had hoped to go up to Hyannis Port
this weekend to spend time with Tish...

1483
01:28:01,640 --> 01:28:04,440
and do some sailing, but I don't think
I'm going to be able to because I'm...

1484
01:28:04,520 --> 01:28:08,480
spending a lot of time
in the office writing testimony
to your committee on cancer clusters.

1485
01:28:08,520 --> 01:28:13,440
Well, l, uh, appreciate
your candor, Skeeter.

1486
01:28:13,480 --> 01:28:16,000
- Anything to be of help, Mr. Chairman.
- Bye.

1487
01:28:19,240 --> 01:28:23,040
[As Warburton] Ah, take off for
the rest of the week, please, Brenda.

1488
01:28:23,120 --> 01:28:25,480
[Dodge] I don't see
how I can help ya on this one.

1489
01:28:25,560 --> 01:28:28,080
This is the EPA.
This is the president.

1490
01:28:28,160 --> 01:28:31,080
- This is my lifeblood.
- Olaf, I see that. I see that.

1491
01:28:31,160 --> 01:28:33,480
But in this town
you've gotta pick your fights.

1492
01:28:33,560 --> 01:28:37,120
This could mean
six figures, Dick.

1493
01:28:39,080 --> 01:28:41,680
High six figures.

1494
01:28:44,080 --> 01:28:47,040
Seven figures?

1495
01:28:50,880 --> 01:28:54,680
I suppose a million dollars
isn't too much to insure against
losin' five billion.

1496
01:28:54,760 --> 01:28:58,440
- Now you're talkin'.
- But how can I funnel
this kind of money to you?

1497
01:28:58,520 --> 01:29:02,880
If that's what you want,
we can find a loophole.
No one will see your fingerprints.

1498
01:29:02,920 --> 01:29:04,960
- No one will know?
- No one will know.

1499
01:29:05,000 --> 01:29:08,560
Olaf's just making a contribution
as a patriotic citizen.

1500
01:29:08,640 --> 01:29:12,840
- And in return for that, he's getting...
- Good government!

1501
01:29:12,880 --> 01:29:15,040
Exactly!
Little access, that's all.

1502
01:29:15,080 --> 01:29:19,080
Yes, I'm callin' from Chairman Dodge's
office on the Hill.

1503
01:29:19,160 --> 01:29:24,200
We wanted to be sure CNN was sending
a crew to the clean air hearings today.

1504
01:29:24,280 --> 01:29:26,600
No, not the new
emission standards.

1505
01:29:26,680 --> 01:29:30,480
We're breaking news.
This is the biggest thing
since the check bouncing scandal.

1506
01:29:30,520 --> 01:29:32,680
This is Cynthia Leeson from
the White House press office.

1507
01:29:32,760 --> 01:29:36,400
My boss just wanted me
to call you folks and let you know
we're going to be making...

1508
01:29:36,480 --> 01:29:40,480
a very important announcement
today at the clean air hearings.

1509
01:29:40,520 --> 01:29:44,880
No, I'm sorry, I can't
tell you that, but it's hot.

1510
01:29:44,960 --> 01:29:47,800
If the New York Times wants to be
the only paper in town to miss out...

1511
01:29:47,880 --> 01:29:50,720
on the biggest story of the year,
that's just up to y'all.

1512
01:29:50,800 --> 01:29:55,120
Hurry up, get into your seats.
Come on, you guys.

1513
01:29:55,200 --> 01:29:57,840
[Hattie] It's gonna be a great day.
Molly, next to Harry.

1514
01:30:00,280 --> 01:30:02,760
- Let's sit here.
- What, in the back?

1515
01:30:02,800 --> 01:30:04,680
- Just sit down, will you?
- All right.

1516
01:30:04,760 --> 01:30:08,840
- How's everything?
- Great.

1517
01:30:08,920 --> 01:30:11,360
You know what would be
a wonderful way for us to start?

1518
01:30:11,440 --> 01:30:15,280
With me congratulating you
on what a wonderful job you've
been doing on the committee.

1519
01:30:15,360 --> 01:30:18,800
And really show our appreciation
especially on behalf
of the minority community.

1520
01:30:18,880 --> 01:30:20,960
Well, I appreciate that, son.
Thank you very much.

1521
01:30:21,040 --> 01:30:23,360
I'm cutting out of here early.

1522
01:30:23,440 --> 01:30:25,360
[Ira]
Don't wanna run into him?

1523
01:30:25,440 --> 01:30:27,360
This is a mistake.
I never should have come.

1524
01:30:27,400 --> 01:30:30,400
I'm surprised, well, delighted
by the media turnout today.

1525
01:30:30,440 --> 01:30:35,080
- I had no idea that clean air
was such a good issue.
- Oh, yeah, isn't it somethin'?

1526
01:30:41,680 --> 01:30:44,080
This meeting of the Power
and Industry Committee...

1527
01:30:44,160 --> 01:30:48,200
to consider the reauthorization
of the clean air act is now in session.

1528
01:30:48,280 --> 01:30:51,080
Today's first business is a panel
of national leaders...

1529
01:30:51,120 --> 01:30:53,840
in the field of utilities,
but before I welcome them,

1530
01:30:53,920 --> 01:30:58,640
the chair would like to yield to the
distinguished gentleman from Florida.

1531
01:30:58,720 --> 01:31:03,000
Thank you, Mr. Chairman.
I'd like to make a very personal
statement, Mr. Chairman.

1532
01:31:03,080 --> 01:31:07,320
I would like to start off by saying
thank you from the bottom of my heart,

1533
01:31:07,400 --> 01:31:11,560
thank you for your leadership
and for your vision.

1534
01:31:11,600 --> 01:31:14,240
But most of all I'd like to
thank you for your courage.

1535
01:31:14,320 --> 01:31:17,360
Especially for your courage.

1536
01:31:17,440 --> 01:31:22,280
- My courage, huh?
- Yes, sir, your courage...

1537
01:31:22,360 --> 01:31:27,240
in exposing the corruption
that eats away at this institution.

1538
01:31:27,320 --> 01:31:29,760
Your courage in taking on
the special interests...

1539
01:31:29,840 --> 01:31:33,760
and your courage in taking
a major new step.

1540
01:31:33,840 --> 01:31:35,760
But l-I've done nothing new.

1541
01:31:35,840 --> 01:31:38,080
Nothing at all.
What are you talking about?

1542
01:31:38,160 --> 01:31:41,800
This is true! Because integrity
is nothing new to you, Mr. Chairman.

1543
01:31:41,840 --> 01:31:44,360
Integrity is second nature
to this man.

1544
01:31:44,440 --> 01:31:47,520
But still it's a rare public servant
who'll take on the PACs...

1545
01:31:47,600 --> 01:31:51,720
and the lobbyists
and the fat cats...

1546
01:31:51,800 --> 01:31:55,080
and side with the American family
who just want to live
in safe neighborhoods...

1547
01:31:55,160 --> 01:31:57,360
and send their kids
off to safe schools.

1548
01:31:57,440 --> 01:32:00,480
Well, I thank the gentleman,
but we really must move along.
If the gentleman would...

1549
01:32:00,560 --> 01:32:03,160
Ladies and gentlemen,
yesterday,

1550
01:32:03,240 --> 01:32:05,760
I had a meeting
with the chairman...

1551
01:32:05,800 --> 01:32:08,080
in his office
with Mr. Olaf Andersen...

1552
01:32:08,160 --> 01:32:11,520
of Gulf Coast Power,
and his lobbyist, Mr. Terry Corrigan.

1553
01:32:11,560 --> 01:32:15,600
I thank the gentleman!
But we really must move along!

1554
01:32:15,680 --> 01:32:17,520
The subject of this meeting...

